==English==

===Etymology===
Greek ''[[suntaxis]]'', from ''[[sun-]]'' 'together' + ''[[tassein]]'' 'arrange'.

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]]:/sɪntæks/

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''syntax''' (uncountable and countable; plural '''[[syntaxes]]''')

# A set of rules that govern how words are combined to form [[phrase]]s and [[sentence]]s.
# The formal rules of a computer language
# The study of the structure of phrases, sentences and language.

